[Black] White’s knight has lunged to e5 and simultaneously threatens both my e5-pawn and a retreat to g-guard Qh5+ possibilities. The straightforward reply is to pry the knight away at once before White can consolidate:

1.  3…d6 gains a tempo by attacking the knight at once;
2.  If 4.Ng4 retreat, White’s central grip is blunted and I keep natural development lines;
3.  I avoid over-materializing lines like 3…Nxe4 4.Nxe5, which cost me the bishop-pair and kingside structure unnecessarily.

Simplest and most principled counter-strike:

[d7d6]
